1998
-----
Hand, foot & mouth disease, fatal - Singapore 19980628100055
Hand, foot & mouth disease - China (Hong Kong) 19980716233251
Hand, foot & mouth disease - China (Hong Kong) (02) 19980729233123
Date: Mon, 31 Jan 2000 11:31:23 +0800
From: Wen-fei Lien <clark10@cdc.gov.tw>

Sentinel physicians reported 121 842 hand, foot & mouth disease (HFMD)
cases between 10 May and 26 December in 1998 in Taiwan, with a peak at the
beginning of June. As contrasted with that the same period in 1999, 63 278
cases were reported, and a smaller peak than that in 1998 appeared at the
end of May. In 1998, there were 405 hospitalized, mostly 5 years old or
younger and 78 of them died.
In contrast, [in 1999 33 hospitalized were recorded, 21of them younger
than 6 months of age, and 6 of [these were dead by 30 December [1999.
--
Wen-fei Lien
Prodirector of disease surveillance department
Centers for Disease Control and Prevention
Taiwan
<clark10@cdc.gov.tw>
